library(tidyverse)

Read in and assign

KaggleMoviesData <- read_csv("data/movies.csv")

 Column specification 
cols(
  original_title = col_character(),
  title = col_character(),
  homepage = col_character(),
  budget = col_double(),
  original_language = col_character(),
  overview = col_character(),
  popularity = col_double(),
  release_date = col_character(),
  revenue = col_double(),
  runtime = col_double(),
  tagline = col_character(),
  vote_average = col_double(),
  vote_count = col_double()
)
KaggleMoviesData
movies_selected <- KaggleMoviesData %>% 
  select("title", "runtime", "budget")
movies_selected
movies_selected %>% 
  filter(is.na(runtime))
movies_runtime <- movies_selected %>% 
  mutate(runtime = na_if(runtime, "0"))
         movies_runtime
# counting missing values
movies_runtime %>% 
  summarise(count = sum(is.na(runtime)))
# replace na observations in the monthly_charges column, with the median of that column
movies_imputed <- movies_runtime %>%
    mutate(runtime = coalesce(runtime, median(runtime, na.rm = TRUE)))

movies_imputed
# counting missing values
movies_imputed %>% 
  summarise(count = sum(is.na(runtime)))

#use the slice_min and slice_max functions on movies_imputed to get the movies with the 10 shortest and 10 longest runtimes.

movies_imputed %>%
  slice_max(runtime, n = 10)
